(6,	'Karmayatra',	4,	'<h3>Karmayatra</h3>\r\n			  <p>Born in a humble Maharashtrian family on January 30, 1951 in Pune, Prakash Javadekar was influenced by the work of RSS (Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh) and became its member.Thereafter, he worked for the Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad (ABVP) before joining the Bharatiya Janata Party which led him towards  path of more than 50 years of Public Life. During all this time he has played various roles in the Party and the Government and shouldered all the responsibilities with utmost sincerity and dedication.</p>',	NULL,	'image',	'karmyatra.jpg',	NULL,	1,	1,	'2020-07-16 19:03:55',	'2020-07-16 13:33:55'),
(7,	'Parliamentarian',	5,	'<p>Parliamentarian Shri Prakash Javadekar started his parliamentarians innings (Rajya Sabha) in March, 2008 when he was nominated and then elected from Maharashtra, his home state. He showed his willingness and earnestness to engage the floor by putting up the right questions on the issues concerning the nation. From the day he was elected to Rajya Sabha in 2008 till 12th February 2014, he raised 691 questions which in itself is a record of sort. For his relentless questioning of the government, 73 Assurances were given by the Government in Rajya Sabha till 5-08-2013. During his Rajya Sabha days from May 2008 to May 2014, he kept on raising questions, mostly in the following segments:</p>',	'q',	'image',	'parli.jpg',	NULL,	1,	1,	'2020-07-16 19:03:55',	'2020-07-16 13:33:55'),
(8,	'Contact Us',	6,	'',	NULL,	'image',	'vid-banner.jpg',	NULL,	1,	1,	'2020-07-16 19:03:55',	'2020-07-16 13:33:55'),
(9,	'Video Gallary',	7,	'',	NULL,	'image',	'video_gallery_banner.jpg',	NULL,	1,	1,	'2020-07-16 19:03:55',	'2020-07-16 13:33:55'),
(10,	'Spokes person',	8,	'',	NULL,	'image',	'spokesperson_banner.jpg',	NULL,	1,	1,	'2020-07-16 19:03:55',	'2020-07-16 13:33:55'),
(11,	'Cabinet Minister',	9,	'2014 General Elections, Shri Narendra Modi became Prime Minister of India with huge and unprecedented mandate. He inducted Shri Javadekar first cabinet as MoS for Environment with Independent Charge and then Union Minister of Human Resource Development on 5th July 2016 where he kept on working till 30th May 2019. In fact, he was given several portfolios as he has been partys crisis manager. For instance, he was appointed Minister of State (Independent Charge)  Environment, Forest & Climate Change on 26th May 2014 to 4th July 2016. He also worked as Minister of State  Parliamentary Affairs from 26th May 2014 to 9th Nov 2014 and Minister of State (Independent Charge)  Information and Broadcasting from 26th May 2014 to 9th Nov 2014',	'',	'image',	'unionbanner-image_(1).jpg',	NULL,	1,	1,	'2020-07-16 19:03:55',	'2020-07-16 13:33:55'),
